race.comment: The well-related SOME STYLE (7) (half to G1 winner Peeping) finally broke the maiden status at the latest effort and will have come on with that win now under the belt. Thompson sticks in the saddle following that last-start victory and looks ready for the step-up in trip now. Very hard to toss. SIAN STAR (2) saves his best form for this circuit with two wins and five placings from just nine spins. Can win without surprising. CANADIAN EXPRESS (4) goes well for hoop Lerena who has two wins and a placing from just four steers. Include in calculations. TAVIS TOWN (1) gets some weight off with the claim and will be cherry-ripe now fourth-up. In the mix. BOVIDAE (5) is usually thereabouts and may earn some minor money.
